---
import PageLayout from '../layouts/PageLayout.astro';

const webpageSchema = {
  '@context': 'https://schema.org',
  '@type': 'WebPage',
  '@id': 'https://chandrakanojia.com/#webpage',
  url: 'https://chandrakanojia.com',
  name: 'Enterprise AI and Regulated Operating Change | Chandra Kanojia',
  description: 'Chandra Kanojia helps large regulated enterprises make AI useful inside CRM, workflow, analytics, service platforms, controls, and operating routines.',
  isPartOf: { '@id': 'https://chandrakanojia.com/#website' },
  about: { '@id': 'https://chandrakanojia.com/#person' }
};

const breadcrumbSchema = {
  '@context': 'https://schema.org',
  '@type': 'BreadcrumbList',
  itemListElement: [
    { '@type': 'ListItem', position: 1, name: 'Home', item: 'https://chandrakanojia.com' }
  ]
};
---
<PageLayout
  title="Enterprise AI and Regulated Operating Change | Chandra Kanojia"
  description="Chandra Kanojia helps large regulated enterprises make AI useful inside CRM, workflow, analytics, service platforms, controls, and operating routines."
  jsonLd={[webpageSchema, breadcrumbSchema]}
>
  <section class="hero" aria-labelledby="hero-title">
    <div class="container hero-grid">
      <div class="hero-main">
        <span class="identity-mark hero-mark" aria-hidden="true"><span></span></span>
        <p class="kicker">Enterprise AI · CRM/Salesforce · Workflow · Regulated Change</p>
        <h1 id="hero-title">Enterprise AI has entered the execution phase.</h1>
        <p class="lead hero-copy">
          Chandra Kanojia helps large regulated enterprises make AI useful inside the systems where work actually moves: CRM, workflow, analytics, service platforms, controls, and operating routines.
        </p>
        <p class="credibility-line">
          The hard part is not access to AI. The hard part is changing work without breaking trust.
        </p>
        <div class="hero-actions">
          <a class="button primary" href="/executive-profile">View Executive Profile</a>
          <a class="button secondary" href="/ai-mandate-studio">Open AI Mandate Studio</a>
        </div>
      </div>
      <aside class="mandate-panel" aria-label="Executive focus">
        <p class="panel-label">Operating focus</p>
        <h2>Make the demo survive contact with real work.</h2>
        <p>
          Useful AI needs more than a model. It needs context, evidence, controls, adoption, and a clear owner for the outcome.
        </p>
      </aside>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section compact" aria-labelledby="authority-title">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="authority-band">
        <p class="band-label" id="authority-title">Operating proof spans</p>
        <p>
          Regulated financial services · Salesforce/CRM modernization · enterprise workflow · service and advisor platforms · analytics and governance · platform reliability · insurance, retirement, brokerage, healthcare, claims, and global consulting transformation.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section" aria-labelledby="mandates-title">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-heading compact-heading">
        <p class="kicker">Where Chandra creates leverage</p>
        <h2 id="mandates-title">The work has to change before AI matters.</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="mandate-grid">
        <article class="mandate-card">
          <span>01</span>
          <h3>Make AI useful beyond the demo</h3>
          <p>Move AI from pilots into real workflows with clear ownership, controls, adoption paths, and business accountability.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="mandate-card">
          <span>02</span>
          <h3>Modernize the systems where work moves</h3>
          <p>Improve CRM, case management, analytics, service platforms, and workflow systems so they guide action instead of only storing activity.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="mandate-card">
          <span>03</span>
          <h3>Create leverage without losing control</h3>
          <p>Reduce friction, increase capacity, improve experience, and strengthen risk discipline inside regulated environments.</p>
        </article>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section alt" aria-labelledby="studio-title">
    <div class="container studio-preview">
      <div class="section-heading compact-heading">
        <p class="kicker">AI Mandate Studio</p>
        <h2 id="studio-title">A safe demo of how the work gets framed.</h2>
        <p>
          This is not a chatbot. It is a curated operating lens. Pick a common enterprise AI mandate and see the questions that decide whether the work can be trusted, funded, and scaled.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="studio-mini-grid">
        <article class="studio-mini-card">
          <h3>AI beyond the demo</h3>
          <p>Where should AI enter the workflow, and where should the human return?</p>
        </article>
        <article class="studio-mini-card">
          <h3>CRM and workflow</h3>
          <p>What should change so the system guides action instead of merely recording activity?</p>
        </article>
        <article class="studio-mini-card">
          <h3>Controls and confidence</h3>
          <p>What evidence, permissions, audit path, and escalation model make AI usable?</p>
        </article>
      </div>
      <a class="button primary" href="/ai-mandate-studio">Open the Studio</a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section" aria-labelledby="insights-title">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-heading">
        <div class="intro">
          <p class="kicker">Field notes</p>
          <h2 id="insights-title">What large enterprises learn after the AI demo.</h2>
        </div>
        <a class="text-link" href="/insights">View insights</a>
      </div>
      <div class="insight-grid">
        <article class="insight-card">
          <p class="tag">Enterprise AI</p>
          <h3><a href="/insights/ai-moved-from-assistance-to-execution-operating-model-has-not">AI Is Moving Faster Than the Enterprise.</a></h3>
          <p>The technology is moving quickly. The harder question is whether the enterprise can change work, governance, and decision-making fast enough to use it well.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="insight-card">
          <p class="tag">CRM</p>
          <h3><a href="/insights/crm-trap-systems-of-record-never-become-systems-of-action">The CRM Trap: When Systems of Record Never Become Systems of Action.</a></h3>
          <p>CRM becomes valuable when it helps the enterprise decide what happens next. Recording activity is not enough.</p>
        </article>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="cta-section" aria-labelledby="cta-title">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="cta-box mandate-cta">
        <div>
          <p class="panel-label">Discuss the mandate</p>
          <h2 id="cta-title">Useful conversations start when the question moves from “Can AI do this?” to “Can the enterprise change the work safely enough to make it matter?”</h2>
          <p>Relevant conversations include AI execution, CRM and workflow modernization, operating leverage in regulated environments, platform reliability, adoption, governance, and executive confidence.</p>
        </div>
        <a class="button" href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/chandra-kanojia/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Connect on LinkedIn</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</PageLayout>
